cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CR, cs.AI 

This paper focuses on the infiltration strategies of socialbots in the Twitter social network, which involves analyzing social interactions and behavior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the potential security threats posed by socialbots, which falls under the category of cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Additionally, the paper uses automated mechanisms and machine learning techniques to generate and analyze data, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of socialbot infiltration on public perception and brand reputation, which could fall under the category of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
